column5: I have fished this spot with Terry, for about the last 6-7 years. This tree was on the brink back  6-7 years ago, of coming down the hill. I took a picture of it today, and it,s still standing tall. Im always keeping one eye on the float and one on the tree.  It,s amazing the strength of the roots .

When the trees are that close brian its not just the strength of the roots, its how intermingled they are.   On the rez I removed about 300 trees on the pow wow site to make room for a new parking lot/camping.  I was kinda shocked and really had to watch what I was doing. Sometimes Id go to remove a tree and another tree 10ft away would start tipping with it
That one will be in the drink like the rest of them were last year (Or was it the year before, lol)

That one will be in the drink like the rest of them were last year (Or was it the year before, lol)  Ya I hear ya Bill. It,s wide open there now, but it wont be when it comes down. Not like I fish there much anymore.
